WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:03.420
[♪ acoustic guitar playing]

2
00:00:09.676 --> 00:00:10.759
[tab clicks]

3
00:00:10.760 --> 00:00:13.763
[♪ "Yahoos and Triangles"
by The Refreshments playing]

4
00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:21.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

5
00:00:27.068 --> 00:00:29.237
♪

6
00:00:35.910 --> 00:00:37.037
[♪ theme song concludes]

7
00:00:37.579 --> 00:00:39.955
Connie. are you still binging <i>Hormonia?</i>

8
00:00:39.956 --> 00:00:41.790
Nah. Too much dong for me.

9
00:00:41.791 --> 00:00:44.501
Counterpoint. There should be more dongs

10
00:00:44.502 --> 00:00:46.545
to make up for the decades
of titties on TV.

11
00:00:46.546 --> 00:00:49.798
I kinda think it's just like
the perfect amount of dong.

12
00:00:49.799 --> 00:00:52.009
These shows are so unrealistic.

13
00:00:52.010 --> 00:00:54.553
People our age just have sex or don't.

14
00:00:54.554 --> 00:00:56.430
- We aren't obsessed about it.
- [door bell jingles]

15
00:00:56.431 --> 00:00:58.975
Who wants to help me get laid
in Mexico this weekend?

16
00:00:59.726 --> 00:01:01.310
What's in Mexico?

17
00:01:01.311 --> 00:01:04.104
A few of the crew guys
told me about this sick deal

18
00:01:04.105 --> 00:01:06.273
for an all-inclusive vacation package.

19
00:01:06.274 --> 00:01:08.275
Ola. do you want to go with me?

20
00:01:08.276 --> 00:01:10.194
No thanks. Joseph.

21
00:01:10.195 --> 00:01:12.529
That would be a pretty intense first date.

22
00:01:12.530 --> 00:01:14.907
Oh. we could smash first.

23
00:01:14.908 --> 00:01:16.492
If that'd make you more comfortable.

24
00:01:16.493 --> 00:01:18.702
You know... it wouldn't.

25
00:01:18.703 --> 00:01:20.037
Had to ask.

26
00:01:20.038 --> 00:01:22.664
Guess it's me and you. Bobby.
You could be my wingman.

27
00:01:22.665 --> 00:01:26.502
Sounds fun. but I was gonna
hang out with Connie this weekend.

28
00:01:26.503 --> 00:01:29.171
I have to finish
that thermo project. remember?

29
00:01:29.172 --> 00:01:32.466
I know. I like watchin' you solder.

30
00:01:32.467 --> 00:01:35.219
She did it in her pajamas last night.

31
00:01:35.220 --> 00:01:37.012
[crunching] What?

32
00:01:37.013 --> 00:01:40.015
I like watchin' too.
She know what she doin'.

33
00:01:40.016 --> 00:01:43.227
Bobby. go. You never take any time off.

34
00:01:43.228 --> 00:01:46.897
That's because with you.
every day is a vacation.

35
00:01:46.898 --> 00:01:48.691
Go to Mexico. please.

36
00:01:48.692 --> 00:01:51.985
Alright! Guys trip to Mexico.

37
00:01:51.986 --> 00:01:53.362
It's gonna be rad!

38
00:01:53.363 --> 00:01:55.447
I'll ditch him if you change your mind.

39
00:01:55.448 --> 00:01:58.200
Even if we're already by the border.
I'll turn around.

40
00:01:58.201 --> 00:02:00.661
[Hank Hill] Why'd you wait
till the day before your trip

41
00:02:00.662 --> 00:02:02.246
to look for your passport?

42
00:02:02.247 --> 00:02:05.916
I've been busy. Dad!
We ran a promotion last month.

43
00:02:05.917 --> 00:02:10.462
Do you know how many people
"bought one to get one"?

44
00:02:10.463 --> 00:02:12.756
Oh. Lord. there it is. Whew.

45
00:02:12.757 --> 00:02:17.052
[laughs]
Those earrings came with the dance moves.

46
00:02:17.053 --> 00:02:20.723
Thank God you grew out
of that South Korean pop phase.

47
00:02:20.724 --> 00:02:23.600
You know. I have a lockbox in the bedroom

48
00:02:23.601 --> 00:02:26.895
where I keep
important documents like my passport

49
00:02:26.896 --> 00:02:29.690
and propane safety certification.

50
00:02:29.691 --> 00:02:31.859
You should get one for your bedroom. too.

51
00:02:31.860 --> 00:02:34.028
Yeah. I'll get around to it.

52
00:02:34.029 --> 00:02:36.363
You're always "getting around" to things.

53
00:02:36.364 --> 00:02:39.491
Did you ever get around
to changing your brake pads?

54
00:02:39.492 --> 00:02:41.952
Oh. wait. No. I did that for you too.

55
00:02:41.953 --> 00:02:44.997
If it wasn't for me.
you'd be rear-ending half of Dallas.

56
00:02:44.998 --> 00:02:47.583
Here. this is a checklist of things

57
00:02:47.584 --> 00:02:50.169
I always do before a trip to Mexico.

58
00:02:50.170 --> 00:02:52.338
You got Mexican car insurance. right?

59
00:02:52.339 --> 00:02:55.799
I already have my own car insurance.
Yours.

60
00:02:55.800 --> 00:02:59.595
No. you're required by law
to have Mexican car insurance

61
00:02:59.596 --> 00:03:01.472
as soon as you cross the border.

62
00:03:01.473 --> 00:03:05.018
I'll get around to--
I mean. I will do it now.

63
00:03:06.269 --> 00:03:08.312
- Dad.
- Yes?

64
00:03:08.313 --> 00:03:12.274
How do I get Mexican car insurance?

65
00:03:12.275 --> 00:03:14.443
Dammit. [sighs] Okay. fine.

66
00:03:14.444 --> 00:03:16.487
I'll take care of the insurance for ya.

67
00:03:16.488 --> 00:03:19.823
If you want to. It's not a big deal. Bye.

68
00:03:19.824 --> 00:03:21.325
[Hank sighs]

69
00:03:21.326 --> 00:03:24.870
I'm the only reason
this whole family isn't dead.

70
00:03:24.871 --> 00:03:27.456
[phone line ringing]

71
00:03:27.457 --> 00:03:30.125
Mexican car insurance.

72
00:03:30.126 --> 00:03:32.628
Agent. Agent!

73
00:03:32.629 --> 00:03:36.090
Let me speak to a gotdang human being!

74
00:03:36.091 --> 00:03:38.842
[♪ "Feels So Good" by Chuck Mangione
hold music plays over phone line]

75
00:03:38.843 --> 00:03:40.929
[humming along]

76
00:03:44.307 --> 00:03:46.684
I guess I could wait a little longer.

77
00:03:46.685 --> 00:03:49.770
[♪ "Feels So Good" continues playing]

78
00:03:49.771 --> 00:03:52.189
Dude! There's a water slide

79
00:03:52.190 --> 00:03:55.067
with a tequila bar at the top
and the bottom.

80
00:03:55.068 --> 00:03:57.361
- [keyboard clicking]
- Good choice on the hotel.

81
00:03:57.362 --> 00:03:59.822
What do you mean.
we don't have a reservation?

82
00:03:59.823 --> 00:04:01.699
Sorry. Señor Gribble. You don't.

83
00:04:01.700 --> 00:04:04.952
Crap. okay. uh... try my alias.

84
00:04:04.953 --> 00:04:06.912
[whispering] Wellington Foulfellow.

85
00:04:06.913 --> 00:04:09.915
- [keyboard clicking]
- That doesn't show up.

86
00:04:09.916 --> 00:04:11.834
Oh. this is so weird.

87
00:04:11.835 --> 00:04:14.211
I remember filling out
the reservation page and everything.

88
00:04:14.212 --> 00:04:15.547
Here it is. See?

89
00:04:16.172 --> 00:04:19.091
Dammit. Joseph. you didn't hit confirm.

90
00:04:19.092 --> 00:04:21.051
<i>- Lo siento.</i>
- Dammit!

91
00:04:21.052 --> 00:04:24.263
We're entirely booked up.
you know. with NurseCon in town.

92
00:04:24.264 --> 00:04:27.850
What... the [bleep]... is NurseCon?

93
00:04:27.851 --> 00:04:30.227
Nurses from all over the world
come into town

94
00:04:30.228 --> 00:04:32.521
- for professional development seminars.
- [nurses chattering]

95
00:04:32.522 --> 00:04:35.107
But between you and me.
it is just an excuse for them

96
00:04:35.108 --> 00:04:37.860
to let loose and make very bad decisions.

97
00:04:37.861 --> 00:04:39.278
[air horn blaring]

98
00:04:39.279 --> 00:04:42.573
[DJ]
Twerking contest starts in 10 minutes!

99
00:04:42.574 --> 00:04:45.200
- [nurses cheering]
- We need two volunteer judges.

100
00:04:45.201 --> 00:04:46.910
Hotel guests only.

101
00:04:46.911 --> 00:04:49.497
- Dammit!
- [sobbing] Oh no.

102
00:04:51.624 --> 00:04:53.292
[♪ upbeat guitar music playing]

103
00:04:53.293 --> 00:04:55.085
[Joseph Gribble] Bobby!

104
00:04:55.086 --> 00:04:56.795
This is Señora Camila.

105
00:04:56.796 --> 00:04:59.131
Joseph. you gotta be...

106
00:04:59.132 --> 00:05:01.675
Miss. hello. I don't know what he--

107
00:05:01.676 --> 00:05:04.053
Señor Foulfellow told me what happened.

108
00:05:04.054 --> 00:05:06.388
Camila and her sister
own a bed and breakfast

109
00:05:06.389 --> 00:05:07.848
and they just had a cancellation.

110
00:05:07.849 --> 00:05:09.641
- Our trip is saved.
- Yes.

111
00:05:09.642 --> 00:05:12.353
And it's up in the mountains.
so you can just follow my car to there.

112
00:05:12.354 --> 00:05:14.188
- [♪ ominous music playing]
- [mirror creaking]

113
00:05:14.189 --> 00:05:17.649
Dude. dude. dude. I don't know
about following a stranger to--

114
00:05:17.650 --> 00:05:19.735
Me and my sister cook all the meals too.

115
00:05:19.736 --> 00:05:22.237
And today. we are making <i>tuétano.</i>

116
00:05:22.238 --> 00:05:24.239
<i>¿Tuétano?</i> Isn't that--

117
00:05:24.240 --> 00:05:25.991
Roasted bone marrow.

118
00:05:25.992 --> 00:05:28.744
Meat butter from the gods.

119
00:05:28.745 --> 00:05:31.288
I-- I mean. I guess
it couldn't hurt to check it out.

120
00:05:31.289 --> 00:05:33.957
- [Joseph softly whooping]
- But Joe. I'm not getting out of the car

121
00:05:33.958 --> 00:05:36.085
until I get eyes on that marrow.

122
00:05:36.086 --> 00:05:37.294
♪

123
00:05:37.295 --> 00:05:39.046
- [TV playing]
- Do you want a snack?

124
00:05:39.047 --> 00:05:42.424
Bobby showed me his recipe
for teriyaki edamame.

125
00:05:42.425 --> 00:05:45.302
Edamame is Japanese for soybeans.

126
00:05:45.303 --> 00:05:47.763
I'm not sure what it means in English.

127
00:05:47.764 --> 00:05:48.973
[phone buzzing]

128
00:05:50.266 --> 00:05:51.767
Hank Hill.

129
00:05:51.768 --> 00:05:53.435
Uh. slow down.

130
00:05:53.436 --> 00:05:56.021
<i>¿Policía?</i> Uh. hold on. please.

131
00:05:56.022 --> 00:05:59.274
It's the Mexican police.
I think Bobby's in trouble.

132
00:05:59.275 --> 00:06:02.277
Hold on. my wife knows Spanish.

133
00:06:02.278 --> 00:06:04.321
<i>- Hola. Me llamo</i> Peggy Hill.
- [TV shuts off]

134
00:06:04.322 --> 00:06:06.740
[Policía] [on phone]
<i>¡Es un emergencia! ¡Fue un accidente!</i>

135
00:06:06.741 --> 00:06:08.325
Mm-mm. wrong number.

136
00:06:08.326 --> 00:06:09.618
<i>- ¡Hasta luego!
-</i> [Policía] <i>¡No!</i>

137
00:06:09.619 --> 00:06:11.995
<i>Listen. your son was in a car accident.</i>

138
00:06:11.996 --> 00:06:14.456
- Oh. no!
- Oh. God. Is he injured?

139
00:06:14.457 --> 00:06:16.917
[Policía]
<i>He is not hurt. but he is at fault.</i>

140
00:06:16.918 --> 00:06:18.794
<i>He's being detained here at the station.</i>

141
00:06:18.795 --> 00:06:20.713
- Can we speak to him?
- [Policía] <i>Yes. of course.</i>

142
00:06:20.714 --> 00:06:22.589
<i>- Here he is.</i>
- [Bobby Hill] <i>Hello.</i>

143
00:06:22.590 --> 00:06:24.341
I know jail can be scary. Bobby.

144
00:06:24.342 --> 00:06:28.470
So. find the biggest. baddest <i>hombre</i>
and punch him right in the face!

145
00:06:28.471 --> 00:06:30.514
What the hell happened. Bobby?

146
00:06:30.515 --> 00:06:33.475
[Bobby] <i>The insurance will cover
the damage to the cars.</i>

147
00:06:33.476 --> 00:06:37.563
<i>but I'm stuck in jail. and I need you
to send me money for bail.</i>

148
00:06:37.564 --> 00:06:39.273
Got dangit. Bobby.

149
00:06:39.274 --> 00:06:43.610
This is exactly the type
of careless behavior I warned you about.

150
00:06:43.611 --> 00:06:46.238
[Bobby]
<i>I just texted you the payment link.</i>

151
00:06:46.239 --> 00:06:49.116
- [taps phone]
- $500?!

152
00:06:49.117 --> 00:06:52.786
[Bobby] <i>Please. hurry.
I don't want to sleep here tonight!</i>

153
00:06:52.787 --> 00:06:54.455
I'm workin' on it! I'm workin' on it!

154
00:06:54.456 --> 00:06:56.665
[Bobby] <i>Thank you. I love you.</i>

155
00:06:56.666 --> 00:06:58.834
I. uh... [sighs]

156
00:06:58.835 --> 00:07:00.961
Well. the important thing
is you're not hurt--

157
00:07:00.962 --> 00:07:03.173
We love you too. son!

158
00:07:03.882 --> 00:07:06.383
- Son?
- Think we got disconnected.

159
00:07:06.384 --> 00:07:08.218
I'll wire the money now.

160
00:07:08.219 --> 00:07:13.140
Bobby was with Joseph.
He might be in trouble too. or dead.

161
00:07:13.141 --> 00:07:16.769
I'm sure Bobby would've said
something if Joseph was dead.

162
00:07:16.770 --> 00:07:18.354
[♪ ominous music plays]

163
00:07:18.355 --> 00:07:20.105
We should check with the Gribbles. Hank.

164
00:07:20.106 --> 00:07:23.525
- [tablet playing indistinctly]
- Nancy! Have you heard from Joseph?

165
00:07:23.526 --> 00:07:25.736
Sure. Sug. I'm talkin' to him right now.

166
00:07:25.737 --> 00:07:28.655
- Say hi to the Hills.
<i>- Hey. Mr. and Mrs. Hill.</i>

167
00:07:28.656 --> 00:07:30.407
Joseph. have you talked to Bobby?

168
00:07:30.408 --> 00:07:33.744
<i>- Uh. yeah.
- Oh. hey. guys!</i>

169
00:07:33.745 --> 00:07:36.914
<i>This is Camila and her sister. Angela.</i>

170
00:07:36.915 --> 00:07:39.166
<i>They own the bed and breakfast
we're staying at.</i>

171
00:07:39.167 --> 00:07:42.211
<i>You have a nice son. Big stomach.</i>

172
00:07:42.212 --> 00:07:44.838
What the hell. Bobby.
why aren't you in jail?

173
00:07:44.839 --> 00:07:47.091
<i>I... uh. what?</i>

174
00:07:47.092 --> 00:07:50.803
You just called me from
a Mexican prison a minute ago.

175
00:07:50.804 --> 00:07:53.597
Did you get the money I wired to ya?
It said it went through.

176
00:07:53.598 --> 00:07:56.601
<i>Dad. I have no idea
what you're talkin' about.</i>

177
00:07:57.602 --> 00:08:01.563
Oh. no. Sugs.
I think y'all have been scammed.

178
00:08:01.564 --> 00:08:04.149
Not me. I said it was a wrong number.

179
00:08:04.150 --> 00:08:05.235
♪

180
00:08:06.528 --> 00:08:08.445
- [♪ upbeat music playing]
- [police siren chirps]

181
00:08:08.446 --> 00:08:10.656
[detective] There was a data breach
at the insurance company.

182
00:08:10.657 --> 00:08:13.283
That's how the scammers
got your information.

183
00:08:13.284 --> 00:08:16.995
But I don't understand.
It sounded just like my son on the phone.

184
00:08:16.996 --> 00:08:20.290
AI cloning.
It's a very common "emergency" scam.

185
00:08:20.291 --> 00:08:24.670
Did you notice "your son" speakin'
in a strange or unnatural manner?

186
00:08:24.671 --> 00:08:27.006
He always talks in a strange manner.

187
00:08:27.007 --> 00:08:30.926
He told us he loved us.
There was nothing unnatural about that.

188
00:08:30.927 --> 00:08:35.180
How did <i>I</i> get scammed?!
There's nobody more cautious than me.

189
00:08:35.181 --> 00:08:37.475
I wear my seatbelt in the car wash.

190
00:08:38.101 --> 00:08:41.353
Sorry. but unfortunately. there's not much
we can do at this point.

191
00:08:41.354 --> 00:08:44.440
This is what my tax dollars
are paying for?

192
00:08:44.441 --> 00:08:48.068
- "Sorry’s" and "unfortunately’s"?
- Wait.

193
00:08:48.069 --> 00:08:52.031
I have one of those
Police Benevolent Association stickers

194
00:08:52.032 --> 00:08:53.490
on my car.

195
00:08:53.491 --> 00:08:55.367
That gets us special treatment. right?

196
00:08:55.368 --> 00:08:57.286
I was saving it for a speeding ticket.

197
00:08:57.287 --> 00:08:59.705
but I have my good looks
to get me out of those.

198
00:08:59.706 --> 00:09:04.084
Best thing we can do is help you
keep this from happenin' again.

199
00:09:04.085 --> 00:09:05.544
Here. take these.

200
00:09:05.545 --> 00:09:06.962
[Hank] A class?

201
00:09:06.963 --> 00:09:09.840
You're not even gonna try
to track this guy down?

202
00:09:09.841 --> 00:09:12.718
Just bust open the door
to his hacking hangout

203
00:09:12.719 --> 00:09:15.596
with one of those new tanks
the department was begging for.

204
00:09:15.597 --> 00:09:18.682
Those tanks are reserved
for the Cowboys parade.

205
00:09:18.683 --> 00:09:20.434
Ugh. Gah.

206
00:09:20.435 --> 00:09:22.227
♪

207
00:09:22.228 --> 00:09:24.980
- [Dale slurping]
- [Hank sighs]

208
00:09:24.981 --> 00:09:27.566
- Yep.
- Don't feel bad. Hank.

209
00:09:27.567 --> 00:09:28.984
It's happened to the best of us.

210
00:09:28.985 --> 00:09:33.031
Can't tell you how many
mail-order bride scams I've fallen for.

211
00:09:34.032 --> 00:09:35.115
It was five.

212
00:09:35.116 --> 00:09:38.035
Worst part is. I have no recourse.

213
00:09:38.036 --> 00:09:40.454
Used to be if a man
stole somethin' from ya.

214
00:09:40.455 --> 00:09:42.581
you'd just find him and whoop his ass.

215
00:09:42.582 --> 00:09:45.376
Then. there was all those times
I was catfished.

216
00:09:45.377 --> 00:09:49.088
Boy. I sent a lot of money
to the Philippines.

217
00:09:49.089 --> 00:09:50.839
Ain't gon' lie. man.
spottin' 'em scammers.

218
00:09:50.840 --> 00:09:52.758
is pretty dang ol' easy. man.
there's somethin' strange

219
00:09:52.759 --> 00:09:56.178
'bout the way them folk talk. man.
Sniff it out every dang ol' time.

220
00:09:56.179 --> 00:09:59.056
If you don't exist.
then you can't get scammed.

221
00:09:59.057 --> 00:10:02.267
I don't pick up the phone.
I don't open any mail.

222
00:10:02.268 --> 00:10:05.646
electronic or snail. or carrier pigeon.

223
00:10:05.647 --> 00:10:07.690
I am an apparition.

224
00:10:07.691 --> 00:10:10.984
If you want. I can help
disappear you too. Hank.

225
00:10:10.985 --> 00:10:13.737
I don't wanna live like that. [sighs]

226
00:10:13.738 --> 00:10:17.741
Luckily. my pen pal.
the Nigerian princess.

227
00:10:17.742 --> 00:10:19.952
warned me about the gift card scam.

228
00:10:19.953 --> 00:10:21.203
♪

229
00:10:21.204 --> 00:10:22.287
[cars honking]

230
00:10:22.288 --> 00:10:23.372
[Bobby] Ow! [groaning]

231
00:10:23.373 --> 00:10:25.916
It even hurts to turn my head.

232
00:10:25.917 --> 00:10:29.211
Sorry!
I didn't know sunscreen could expire.

233
00:10:29.212 --> 00:10:31.630
I mean. I used it. too. and I'm fine.

234
00:10:31.631 --> 00:10:33.048
Whatever.

235
00:10:33.049 --> 00:10:36.176
Swing through Arlen on the way back
so I can check on my dad.

236
00:10:36.177 --> 00:10:38.470
I feel bad he was scammed.

237
00:10:38.471 --> 00:10:40.973
- Shit.
- What now?

238
00:10:40.974 --> 00:10:44.059
Uh. I forgot my passport.
We gotta turn around.

239
00:10:44.060 --> 00:10:47.521
No. no. no. Look down. it's in your lap.

240
00:10:47.522 --> 00:10:49.273
Uh. how long has it been there?

241
00:10:49.274 --> 00:10:50.899
[groaning]

242
00:10:50.900 --> 00:10:52.819
[♪ gentle guitar music playing]

243
00:10:53.403 --> 00:10:57.906
Hank? Why are we in a room
filled with octogenarians?

244
00:10:57.907 --> 00:11:00.784
Excuse me. I'm only 76.

245
00:11:00.785 --> 00:11:03.412
And you still have your hearing.
Good for you!

246
00:11:03.413 --> 00:11:05.873
Ahem. welcome to SAPS.

247
00:11:05.874 --> 00:11:08.250
Seniors Against Phishers and Scammers.

248
00:11:08.251 --> 00:11:11.920
Here. we will teach you the tools to live
cyber-safe. healthy digital lives.

249
00:11:11.921 --> 00:11:13.797
[Peggy Hill] Oh. oh! Excuse me.

250
00:11:13.798 --> 00:11:15.883
Please save your questions
until the end of--

251
00:11:15.884 --> 00:11:20.262
I just wanted to point out
that I am not a senior.

252
00:11:20.263 --> 00:11:22.723
as the name of this class implies.

253
00:11:22.724 --> 00:11:26.060
Okay. but you're still here
because you've been scammed.

254
00:11:26.061 --> 00:11:29.229
No. my husband was. Right. Hank?

255
00:11:29.230 --> 00:11:30.981
[sighing] Uh... yeah.

256
00:11:30.982 --> 00:11:33.233
Well. perhaps you could
support your husband

257
00:11:33.234 --> 00:11:36.695
and all these other people.
and quietly lead by example.

258
00:11:36.696 --> 00:11:39.573
I know what you're doing.
and I will allow it.

259
00:11:39.574 --> 00:11:41.658
- If there are no other concerns--
- Yeah. uh.

260
00:11:41.659 --> 00:11:45.120
I have a concern about something
you said a second ago.

261
00:11:45.121 --> 00:11:48.999
See. I'm not interested
in living a "healthy digital life."

262
00:11:49.000 --> 00:11:51.960
I just wanna learn how
to track down these criminals

263
00:11:51.961 --> 00:11:53.671
so I can kick their asses.

264
00:11:53.672 --> 00:11:55.881
Sir. over three million Americans

265
00:11:55.882 --> 00:11:59.009
are victims of fraud every year.
and less than 1% of those cases

266
00:11:59.010 --> 00:12:01.220
- have ever been solved.
- [Hank groaning]

267
00:12:01.221 --> 00:12:03.681
I know you all wanna take action
and go on the offensive.

268
00:12:03.682 --> 00:12:06.433
but when it comes to cyber safety.
the best offense

269
00:12:06.434 --> 00:12:08.977
is a good defense. just like football.

270
00:12:08.978 --> 00:12:11.355
Or is it the other way around in football?

271
00:12:11.356 --> 00:12:12.731
[chuckles] I'm more of a chess fan.

272
00:12:12.732 --> 00:12:15.484
- [under breath] I should kick his ass.
- What was that?

273
00:12:15.485 --> 00:12:18.445
[loudly] He said he wanted
to kick the instructor's ass!

274
00:12:18.446 --> 00:12:20.030
[group murmuring]

275
00:12:20.031 --> 00:12:23.158
Now. this is an image of a phishing email.

276
00:12:23.159 --> 00:12:25.828
There are several obvious clues
which indicate that.

277
00:12:25.829 --> 00:12:28.498
Mr. Hill. can you identify any of them?

278
00:12:29.332 --> 00:12:31.709
Uh... I'm not sure. I guess. uh--

279
00:12:31.710 --> 00:12:33.627
The sender's address is fake.

280
00:12:33.628 --> 00:12:35.546
Yes. Good eye. Maryann.

281
00:12:35.547 --> 00:12:39.842
An email like crypto_king@starwave.mobi
is a big red flag.

282
00:12:39.843 --> 00:12:42.845
Mr. Hill. someone with delayed
tech literacy like yourself

283
00:12:42.846 --> 00:12:45.431
may need the aid
of some anti-scam software.

284
00:12:45.432 --> 00:12:47.683
We happen to sell one for $99.99.

285
00:12:47.684 --> 00:12:51.812
Well. I guess this is cheaper
than the 500 I lost to the scammer.

286
00:12:51.813 --> 00:12:54.273
No. this is a scam! I was testing you.

287
00:12:54.274 --> 00:12:56.859
There-- there's even a picture
of a Trojan horse on the box.

288
00:12:56.860 --> 00:12:58.736
My Lord. you nearly lost your money again.

289
00:12:58.737 --> 00:13:01.572
Why would I think
<i>you're</i> trying to scam me?

290
00:13:01.573 --> 00:13:04.908
Will my husband's incompetency
affect my grade?

291
00:13:04.909 --> 00:13:07.829
- [♪ upbeat music playing]
- [drill whirring]

292
00:13:09.289 --> 00:13:12.624
Hey. Dad. I got you a gift from Mexico.

293
00:13:12.625 --> 00:13:16.587
It's a shot glass that says.
"Tequila made me do it."

294
00:13:16.588 --> 00:13:20.090
- Just put it down over there.
- Okay.

295
00:13:20.091 --> 00:13:23.469
So. I just stopped by
to see how you were feelin'.

296
00:13:23.470 --> 00:13:26.513
[Hank] Well. I'm still upset with you.
if that's what you're asking.

297
00:13:26.514 --> 00:13:30.893
Wait. you're upset with <i>me</i>
because <i>you</i> got scammed?

298
00:13:30.894 --> 00:13:33.103
I only got scammed because I thought

299
00:13:33.104 --> 00:13:36.398
- you were being irresponsible again.
- Again?

300
00:13:36.399 --> 00:13:39.777
- What is that supposed to mean?
- You forgot the list.

301
00:13:39.778 --> 00:13:43.906
If you had taken it. you would've seen
that item 12 was bring sunscreen.

302
00:13:43.907 --> 00:13:47.159
and you wouldn't have come back
lookin' like a damn fire hydrant.

303
00:13:47.160 --> 00:13:50.245
Huh! Maybe I should make <i>you</i> a list.

304
00:13:50.246 --> 00:13:53.415
Don't worry. it's way shorter
than the one you made.

305
00:13:53.416 --> 00:13:56.835
Number one. don't get scammed. That's it.

306
00:13:56.836 --> 00:13:59.546
I was trying to keep you safe. as always.

307
00:13:59.547 --> 00:14:02.299
I'm the guy that keeps us
prepared and protected.

308
00:14:02.300 --> 00:14:05.595
Well. maybe you aren't that guy anymore!

309
00:14:06.638 --> 00:14:09.973
I gotta go. Have fun with your holes.

310
00:14:09.974 --> 00:14:12.059
I will. I always do.

311
00:14:12.060 --> 00:14:15.104
[♪ somber guitar music playing]

312
00:14:15.105 --> 00:14:17.231
[sighs]

313
00:14:17.232 --> 00:14:18.399
[insects chirping]

314
00:14:18.400 --> 00:14:20.026
♪

315
00:14:21.069 --> 00:14:22.486
- [groans]
- [door opens]

316
00:14:22.487 --> 00:14:25.322
I had a feeling you'd be here.

317
00:14:25.323 --> 00:14:28.325
Also. I saw you on my infrared cameras.

318
00:14:28.326 --> 00:14:31.662
Just teach me
how not to get scammed again.

319
00:14:31.663 --> 00:14:34.331
I'm not lookin' to go full Gribble.

320
00:14:34.332 --> 00:14:36.458
[♪ mysterious music plays]

321
00:14:36.459 --> 00:14:39.503
[on computer] <i>Hello. I'm Hank Hill
and I think propane</i>

322
00:14:39.504 --> 00:14:41.797
<i>is the devil's oxygen.</i>

323
00:14:41.798 --> 00:14:45.342
I would never say that!
How is this even legal?

324
00:14:45.343 --> 00:14:47.970
This is a parody. Fair use. baby.

325
00:14:47.971 --> 00:14:49.471
- Watch this.
- [mouse clicking]

326
00:14:49.472 --> 00:14:51.140
<i>I'm Bill Dauterive.</i>

327
00:14:51.141 --> 00:14:54.560
<i>I have both human and feline genitalia.</i>

328
00:14:54.561 --> 00:14:57.646
[laughs] Come on. that's funny.

329
00:14:57.647 --> 00:15:01.608
You made AI renderings
of everyone in the neighborhood?

330
00:15:01.609 --> 00:15:04.611
Only the ones dumb enough
to let me record them.

331
00:15:04.612 --> 00:15:08.824
<i>You made AI renderings of everyone
in the neighborhood?</i>

332
00:15:08.825 --> 00:15:11.577
- Stop that.
- I'm just trying to show you.

333
00:15:11.578 --> 00:15:14.663
this is how those scammers
tricked you with Bobby's voice.

334
00:15:14.664 --> 00:15:17.416
- Anyone can do it.
- Anyone?

335
00:15:17.417 --> 00:15:19.960
It's a depraved new world. Hank.

336
00:15:19.961 --> 00:15:23.005
That's why you need to live
in the shadows like me.

337
00:15:23.006 --> 00:15:27.426
I scrub the internet every single day
to erase my digital footprints.

338
00:15:27.427 --> 00:15:31.096
I create and kill off
a new alias every week.

339
00:15:31.097 --> 00:15:35.225
and I always wear polymer gloves
if I touch anything.

340
00:15:35.226 --> 00:15:37.019
including myself.

341
00:15:37.020 --> 00:15:40.272
- Okay. that's enough.
- You think I'm crazy. don't you?

342
00:15:40.273 --> 00:15:43.525
But guess who's never
been scammed or phished.

343
00:15:43.526 --> 00:15:45.361
or had his identity stolen?

344
00:15:45.362 --> 00:15:47.863
Cleverton Wiswall!

345
00:15:47.864 --> 00:15:51.617
So. who's crazy now. Hank Hill?
Social security number 263--

346
00:15:51.618 --> 00:15:55.412
Okay. okay. I get it.
Show me what I need to do.

347
00:15:55.413 --> 00:15:58.123
Welcome to the Dale side. Hank.

348
00:15:58.124 --> 00:16:00.377
[laughing maniacally]

349
00:16:02.295 --> 00:16:04.380
[coughing]

350
00:16:04.381 --> 00:16:07.384
[AI laughing maniacally]

351
00:16:10.720 --> 00:16:12.262
- [birds chirping]
- [kids chattering]

352
00:16:12.263 --> 00:16:15.100
[♪ "Paranoid" by Black Sabbath playing]

353
00:16:16.142 --> 00:16:18.103
- [keyboard clacking]
- [mouse clicks]

354
00:16:21.147 --> 00:16:26.361
<i>♪ Finished with my woman 'cause she
couldn't help me with my mind ♪</i>

355
00:16:26.695 --> 00:16:29.196
<i>♪ People think I'm insane ♪</i>

356
00:16:29.197 --> 00:16:32.575
- [gasps]
<i>- ♪ Because I am frowning all the time ♪</i>

357
00:16:34.661 --> 00:16:36.663
[computer keyboard clicking]

358
00:16:37.914 --> 00:16:40.333
<i>♪ Oh. yeah ♪</i>

359
00:16:41.668 --> 00:16:42.751
[Peggy gasps lightly]

360
00:16:42.752 --> 00:16:43.961
[phone hangs up]

361
00:16:43.962 --> 00:16:45.671
What the hell. Hank?

362
00:16:45.672 --> 00:16:46.756
[Peggy scoffs]

363
00:16:49.175 --> 00:16:51.218
- [machine beeps]
- [Hank] Hi. you've reached the home

364
00:16:51.219 --> 00:16:53.722
of. uh. two random people.

365
00:16:54.723 --> 00:16:58.100
You sure you wanna use your own voice?

366
00:16:58.101 --> 00:17:00.310
- [machine beeps]
- Hello. you've reached the home

367
00:17:00.311 --> 00:17:03.439
of my neighbors. the. uh. human family.

368
00:17:03.440 --> 00:17:05.107
[♪ song ends]

369
00:17:05.108 --> 00:17:06.734
[insects chirping]

370
00:17:06.735 --> 00:17:09.820
- [elevator dings]
- Then he started taking it out on me.

371
00:17:09.821 --> 00:17:11.405
like it was <i>my</i> fault.

372
00:17:11.406 --> 00:17:14.533
You should cut your dad some slack.
He's just shaken up.

373
00:17:14.534 --> 00:17:18.579
I can tell you're distracted too.
You haven't even kissed me hello yet.

374
00:17:18.580 --> 00:17:22.624
Sorry. just-- ah. my lips
are sunburned too.

375
00:17:22.625 --> 00:17:24.251
Oh. screw it.

376
00:17:24.252 --> 00:17:26.045
[both] Mm.

377
00:17:26.046 --> 00:17:28.172
Ooh! Worth it.

378
00:17:28.173 --> 00:17:29.174
[door creaks]

379
00:17:31.051 --> 00:17:33.510
[Connie Souphanousinphone]
Why is it so dark in here?

380
00:17:33.511 --> 00:17:35.388
[switch clicking]

381
00:17:37.182 --> 00:17:40.643
[♪ dramatic music playing]

382
00:17:45.065 --> 00:17:47.232
[gasps] We've been robbed!

383
00:17:47.233 --> 00:17:49.694
[Joseph groaning]

384
00:17:50.695 --> 00:17:52.071
[weakly] Help me.

385
00:17:52.072 --> 00:17:55.366
- What the hell happened?
- The power went out.

386
00:17:55.367 --> 00:17:57.826
so I had to eat all the food
before it went bad.

387
00:17:57.827 --> 00:18:00.621
But you ate all the food
out of the cupboards. too.

388
00:18:00.622 --> 00:18:03.415
The power was out in the cupboards too.

389
00:18:03.416 --> 00:18:06.043
You forgot to pay
the electric bill. didn't you?

390
00:18:06.044 --> 00:18:08.796
I reminded you 100 times.

391
00:18:08.797 --> 00:18:11.924
Oh. that's what's so weird. I did pay it.

392
00:18:11.925 --> 00:18:14.968
I even remember entering my credit card...

393
00:18:14.969 --> 00:18:16.887
Oh. I see what happened. [chuckles]

394
00:18:16.888 --> 00:18:18.430
You're gonna find this funny.

395
00:18:18.431 --> 00:18:20.933
I forgot to hit confirm again.

396
00:18:20.934 --> 00:18:22.685
Got dangit. Joseph.

397
00:18:22.686 --> 00:18:24.520
Oh. it's no big deal. I'll confirm it now.

398
00:18:24.521 --> 00:18:26.356
See? All taken care of.

399
00:18:27.732 --> 00:18:30.901
I gotta be honest. I thought the lights
would turn right back on.

400
00:18:30.902 --> 00:18:34.196
Ugh. I've had it!
You are way too irresponsible.

401
00:18:34.197 --> 00:18:37.991
Hey. chill.
They'll probably be back on by tomorrow.

402
00:18:37.992 --> 00:18:40.285
It's not just that. It's everything.

403
00:18:40.286 --> 00:18:43.205
The expired sunscreen.
the hotel reservation--

404
00:18:43.206 --> 00:18:45.374
Okay. Okay. I-- I know you're mad

405
00:18:45.375 --> 00:18:49.211
and I'm happy to talk about it
right after I throw up again.

406
00:18:49.212 --> 00:18:51.214
[gagging]

407
00:18:52.382 --> 00:18:55.217
- [Joseph retching]
- [Bobby sighs]

408
00:18:55.218 --> 00:18:58.303
- You alright?
- I see now why my dad

409
00:18:58.304 --> 00:19:00.514
- gets so frustrated with me.
- [retching continues]

410
00:19:00.515 --> 00:19:04.852
It's exactly how I feel about Joseph
droppin' the ball all weekend.

411
00:19:04.853 --> 00:19:07.730
So. like. I'm Joseph... to my dad.

412
00:19:07.731 --> 00:19:11.275
- [Joseph] [retching] Oh. it's so much!
- Wow. good analogy.

413
00:19:11.276 --> 00:19:14.653
I'd be turned on if you didn't look
like a paper-maché volcano.

414
00:19:14.654 --> 00:19:17.114
Oh man. I-- I may have gone too far

415
00:19:17.115 --> 00:19:20.159
tellin' my dad
that he couldn't protect us anymore.

416
00:19:20.160 --> 00:19:22.995
My mom said he was actin'
pretty nutty after that.

417
00:19:22.996 --> 00:19:25.122
like. Mr. Gribble nutty.

418
00:19:25.123 --> 00:19:26.498
Yikes.

419
00:19:26.499 --> 00:19:29.168
But. hey. he's always been
a reasonable man.

420
00:19:29.169 --> 00:19:31.045
I'm sure he'll come to his senses.

421
00:19:31.046 --> 00:19:34.591
- [♪ dramatic music playing]
- [motor whirring]

422
00:19:35.008 --> 00:19:36.051
[flame whooshes]

423
00:19:36.593 --> 00:19:37.968
[fire crackling]

424
00:19:37.969 --> 00:19:39.887
[Peggy] Hank. you have a call!

425
00:19:39.888 --> 00:19:41.638
What? No.

426
00:19:41.639 --> 00:19:44.933
What the hell. Peggy?
I told you not to answer the phone.

427
00:19:44.934 --> 00:19:47.102
We are not going to live
the rest of our lives

428
00:19:47.103 --> 00:19:50.189
afraid of every call that comes in.

429
00:19:50.190 --> 00:19:54.443
Besides. you are going to
want to talk to this person.

430
00:19:54.444 --> 00:19:56.195
- Hello?
- [voice] <i>Hank Hill?</i>

431
00:19:56.196 --> 00:19:57.821
<i>This is Sly Stallone.</i>

432
00:19:57.822 --> 00:20:00.908
<i>I'm callin' all my biggest fans
such as yourself</i>

433
00:20:00.909 --> 00:20:04.745
<i>to tell you that I'm doing
a sequel to</i> Over the Top.

434
00:20:04.746 --> 00:20:08.540
Really? Well. uh.
that's interesting. Mr. Stallone.

435
00:20:08.541 --> 00:20:10.292
See? I told you!

436
00:20:10.293 --> 00:20:12.753
If you don't mind me asking.
how did you get my number?

437
00:20:12.754 --> 00:20:15.381
<i>From your profile on the</i> Over the Top...

438
00:20:15.382 --> 00:20:17.216
[Bobby and Sly's voice]
...fan club website.

439
00:20:17.217 --> 00:20:20.678
You used to be very active
on the message boards.

440
00:20:20.679 --> 00:20:23.722
[Hank] <i>And what was my username
on those message boards?</i>

441
00:20:23.723 --> 00:20:26.767
- [Sly's voice] <i>Hank Hill.</i>
- Could have been a lucky guess.

442
00:20:26.768 --> 00:20:29.687
[Sly's voice] <i>Anyway. Hank.
I'm offering an exciting opportunity</i>

443
00:20:29.688 --> 00:20:32.564
<i>to a select few super fans
to be a producer</i>

444
00:20:32.565 --> 00:20:35.693
<i>on</i> Over the Top 2: Arm-ageddon.

445
00:20:35.694 --> 00:20:38.487
[Bobby and Sly's voice]
And if you contribute $10.000.

446
00:20:38.488 --> 00:20:40.823
you'll get a co-executive producer credit.

447
00:20:40.824 --> 00:20:43.742
He's asking for money. That's a red flag.

448
00:20:43.743 --> 00:20:47.871
But you gotta act fast.
There's only one co-EP credit left.

449
00:20:47.872 --> 00:20:50.374
They don't just give those out
in Hollywood. you know.

450
00:20:50.375 --> 00:20:52.835
And now. he's doin'
the time pressure thing.

451
00:20:52.836 --> 00:20:54.461
He's goin' right by the book.

452
00:20:54.462 --> 00:20:57.631
Well. Hank. what is your gut telling you?

453
00:20:57.632 --> 00:21:00.552
[♪ gentle guitar music playing]

454
00:21:01.052 --> 00:21:03.470
Mr. Stallone. I'm in.

455
00:21:03.471 --> 00:21:07.266
This country needs
a blue-collar arm-wrestling hero

456
00:21:07.267 --> 00:21:08.767
[over phone] <i>now more than ever.</i>

457
00:21:08.768 --> 00:21:12.271
Oh. uh. wow. Mr. Hill.
you really are a true fan.

458
00:21:12.272 --> 00:21:15.816
Say. will you be drivin'
that box van from the original?

459
00:21:15.817 --> 00:21:19.945
Uh. yeah. I can't wait to drive
that thing again.

460
00:21:19.946 --> 00:21:22.031
thanks to your contribution.

461
00:21:22.032 --> 00:21:24.575
And you know how much
I'd like to contribute?

462
00:21:24.576 --> 00:21:26.076
Jack squat.

463
00:21:26.077 --> 00:21:28.912
You drove an 18-wheeler in that movie.

464
00:21:28.913 --> 00:21:31.373
not some rolling toaster.

465
00:21:31.374 --> 00:21:34.168
I must have forgot that.

466
00:21:34.169 --> 00:21:37.880
Well. I don't see how.
Your character's big rig was iconic.

467
00:21:37.881 --> 00:21:42.176
You got me.
I'm not the real Sylvester Stallone.

468
00:21:42.177 --> 00:21:43.510
No. you're not.

469
00:21:43.511 --> 00:21:44.803
[♪ inspiring music playing]

470
00:21:44.804 --> 00:21:47.848
You know. the real Sylvester Stallone
should kick your ass

471
00:21:47.849 --> 00:21:51.352
for misusing his good name.
and I'd join him if I could.

472
00:21:51.353 --> 00:21:53.354
Please don't kick my ass. sir.

473
00:21:53.355 --> 00:21:56.648
Look. whoever you are.
you should be ashamed of yourself.

474
00:21:56.649 --> 00:21:58.984
Why don't you do somethin'
productive with your life?

475
00:21:58.985 --> 00:22:02.196
Take my son. He seemed like a lost cause.

476
00:22:02.197 --> 00:22:04.866
but he ended up finding somethin'
he's damn good at.

477
00:22:05.867 --> 00:22:09.286
Now I'm gonna do the modern version
of kicking your ass.

478
00:22:09.287 --> 00:22:12.956
I'm blocking your number
and reporting it as spam.

479
00:22:12.957 --> 00:22:14.917
Goodbye.

480
00:22:14.918 --> 00:22:16.502
- Hoyeah!
- [Bobby] Yes!

481
00:22:16.503 --> 00:22:19.505
I knew my dad's instincts
would kick back in.

482
00:22:19.506 --> 00:22:21.006
Thank you. Connie.

483
00:22:21.007 --> 00:22:23.759
Your mom did a good job
playing her part. too.

484
00:22:23.760 --> 00:22:25.886
She told me she spent three hours

485
00:22:25.887 --> 00:22:29.139
gettin' into her favorite character.
Herself.

486
00:22:29.140 --> 00:22:33.185
Now. let's use AI to call my dad
as Jackie Chan.

487
00:22:33.186 --> 00:22:34.604
♪

488
00:22:34.938 --> 00:22:37.731
Your password manager is all set.

489
00:22:37.732 --> 00:22:41.735
And to access this.
I need to use a stupid authenticator app?

490
00:22:41.736 --> 00:22:43.904
Don't worry. you'll get used to it.

491
00:22:43.905 --> 00:22:48.033
Just think of this like a lockbox
for your online valuables.

492
00:22:48.034 --> 00:22:50.494
The cyber-safety guy
said that every family

493
00:22:50.495 --> 00:22:52.955
should have a code word
for suspicious calls.

494
00:22:52.956 --> 00:22:55.582
What do we think of "kumquats"?

495
00:22:55.583 --> 00:22:57.501
- [laptop shuts]
- I'm not sayin' that word.

496
00:22:57.502 --> 00:23:00.129
Fine. I made a whole list of options.

497
00:23:00.130 --> 00:23:02.256
How about "kiwi"?

498
00:23:02.257 --> 00:23:05.801
- Does it have to be fruit?
- What about "serendipity"?

499
00:23:05.802 --> 00:23:08.929
That's a cool word and a decent movie.

500
00:23:08.930 --> 00:23:10.973
Wrong on both accounts.

501
00:23:10.974 --> 00:23:13.183
Just stop me when you hear
something you like.

502
00:23:13.184 --> 00:23:15.519
Here we go. "Quaint."

503
00:23:15.520 --> 00:23:18.731
- "February." "Hat."
- "Monkey!"

504
00:23:18.732 --> 00:23:21.442
Uh-uh. wait your turn. son. "Needle."

505
00:23:21.443 --> 00:23:23.193
"Noodle." "Spectacles..."

506
00:23:23.194 --> 00:23:25.654
This is somethin'
I wouldn't mind letting AI handle.

507
00:23:25.655 --> 00:23:27.031
- [Peggy] "Paddle."
- [Bobby laughing]

508
00:23:27.032 --> 00:23:29.950
[Peggy] "Carnitas." "Chupacabra."

509
00:23:29.951 --> 00:23:33.996
<i>"Toblerone." "Beefsteak." "Herbivore."</i>

510
00:23:33.997 --> 00:23:37.041
<i>"Acquaintanceship." "Didgeridoo."</i>

511
00:23:37.042 --> 00:23:40.210
<i>"Smock." "Flibbertigibbet."</i>

512
00:23:40.211 --> 00:23:43.130
<i>"Cooperation." "Bundt."</i>

513
00:23:43.131 --> 00:23:46.342
<i>"Ukulele." "Chimichanga."</i>

514
00:23:46.343 --> 00:23:50.262
<i>"Waddle." "Hallelujah." "Polyp."</i>

515
00:23:50.263 --> 00:23:53.349
<i>"Iridescent." "Jaunty."</i>

516
00:23:53.350 --> 00:23:56.685
<i>"Lounge wear." "Horticulture."</i>

517
00:23:56.686 --> 00:23:59.563
<i>"Goggles." "Knockwurst."</i>

518
00:23:59.564 --> 00:24:02.358
<i>"Hubba Bubba." "Popcorn."</i>

519
00:24:02.359 --> 00:24:05.152
<i>"Cabbage." "Zoink."</i>

520
00:24:05.153 --> 00:24:08.238
<i>"Wabi Sabi." "Dracula."</i>

521
00:24:08.239 --> 00:24:10.908
<i>"Luminescence." "Scam."</i>

522
00:24:10.909 --> 00:24:11.992
[birds chirping]

523
00:24:11.993 --> 00:24:13.911
- [golf club thumps]
- [crowd cheering]

524
00:24:13.912 --> 00:24:15.954
♪

525
00:24:15.955 --> 00:24:18.957
[Hank] <i>You know how much
I'd like to contribute? Jack squat.</i>

526
00:24:18.958 --> 00:24:21.961
[♪ fanfare playing]

526
